OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782487105
OL,3,CRed weather warnings remain in place
OL,4,Cas hospitals declare critical incidents
OL,6,FThe Met Office said temperatures had
OL,7,Freached 36.7C in Merryfield, Somerset,
OL,8,Fon Thursday afternoon, provisionally
OL,9,Fmaking it the UK's hottest June day on
OL,10,Frecord.
OL,12,FSchools and nurseries were forced to
OL,13,Fclosed and a hosepipe ban was brought
OL,14,Fin for Kent amid surging demand.
OL,16,FAlcohol and exercise warnings
OL,18,FA chief at the country's largest
OL,19,Fambulance service has warned people to
OL,20,Fdrink responsibly and avoid exercising
OL,21,Fin the continuing high temperatures.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
