OL,3,CRed weather warnings remain in place
OL,4,Cas hospitals declare critical incidents
OL,6,FCurrent UK weather conditions are
OL,7,Fperfect for a surge in mosquitoes,
OL,8,Fleading to bites, an expert has warned.
OL,10,FThose capable of carrying nasty
OL,11,Fillnesses, such as dengue fever and
OL,12,FZika, could also take hold in the UK
OL,13,Fin the coming years due to climate
OL,14,Fchange, according to Dr Mojca Kristan,
OL,15,Fassistant professor in medical
OL,16,Fentomology at the London School of
OL,17,FHygiene and Tropical Medicine (LSHTM).
OL,19,FShe suggested people should take
OL,20,Fprecautions to ensure they are not
OL,21,Fbitten.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30413
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782487105
OL,3,CRed weather warnings remain in place
OL,4,Cas hospitals declare critical incidents
OL,6,F"To protect yourself from bites, wear
OL,7,Finsect repellent and cover your skin
OL,8,Fwith long sleeves, plus wear socks in
OL,9,Fthe evening as mosquitoes like biting
OL,10,Faround ankles," she said.
